{
  "stem": "13981.5",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he's about the only one.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There is a lady, I told you before.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 49,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Lizzie [INAUDIBLE] was a secretary, but whom I did not know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 50,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Washington.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was quite a reunion of some of the details that came out, for instance, about Hitler's death, that I didn't know about; Goering's death, how did he get the capsule.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the doctor, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] I think Dr.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Lattimer, ?] told me-- or told us as a group, that Goering, while he was prisoner, always complained about chapped lips.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And his skin was all red.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He had a rash.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the guards became so used to his going to the other room, wherever it was, to get his [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] skin ointments, or whatever it was, that they didn't realize that that was the place where he kept his cyanide capsule.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "See, they had been bodily searched everywhere in the room, searched daily for cyanide, for the capsules.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that's where he kept it, and he dug it out of this jar.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that's how he, a few minutes before being, supposed to have been, hanged, got his jar out of there, bit it, and of course, died.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 52,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Just about two weeks ago.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 53,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Another thing I learned that I hadn't known is that-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I always had thought that after Hitler married Eva Braun, that he gave orders to his troops that when he and Eva were to leave the bunker where there were, to shoot them and then douse their bodies with gasoline and burn them.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But this same doctor told me something completely different.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 54,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Hitler actually used a cyanide capsule, bit it, and the second he bit it, also fired a pistol into-- a shot into his head.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
